tweet:
CLOUD FONTS? Get em all-run this Macro

counter = 1 
For Each fontID In Application.FontNames

ActiveDocument.Content.InsertAfter Text:=fontID
ActiveDocument.Paragraphs(counter).Range.Font.Name = fontID
counter = counter +  1 
ActiveDocument.Content.InsertAfter Text:=vbCrLf

Next

Tips For @Shopify Store Owners

name: Mitch Kosterman
description:

#ActuallyAutistic
tweet:
Tips For @Shopify Store Owners
Careful of starting with a large (over 500) inventory. You will have things to learn and sort out. Start with about a five choice menu and keep your vendors to a dozen or less, is my best advice. Run for 6 months then add in stuff.

name: Mitch Kosterman
description:

tweet:
Tips For @Shopify Store Owners
If you plan to ship worldwide and not all your vendors do, you may want to consider putting that limitation in the individual product listing to avoid customer frustration.

description:

#ActuallyAutistic
tweet:
Tips For @Shopify Store Owners
My best advice: Skip the AliBaba stuff. Too unreliable and sketchy. That means not using @OberloApp which will make your life simpler. In spite of the sometimes thick support people, at least @spocket peeps will answer you and try to help.

name: Mitch Kosterman
description:
Actor, Traveller, Writer, Producer, Director, Grampa, Photographer
#ActuallyAutistic
tweet:
Tips For @Shopify Store Owners
RE: @spocketofficial
Limit your list of vendors to reliable ones that have a significant number of items you want in your store, have good margins and solid shipping profiles (i.e. cheap, fast, global).

name: Mitch Kosterman
description:
Actor, Traveller, Writer, Producer, Director, Grampa, Photographer
#ActuallyAutistic
tweet:
Tips For @Shopify Store Owners
RE: @spocketofficial
Pay attention to the specific vendor's shipping. Usually, a vendor's shipping is consistent across its product line. Sometimes, you will decide not to use that vendor because of shipping costs, global reach or shipping delay.

name: Mitch Kosterman
description:

#ActuallyAutistic
tweet:

Does not exist... Anywhere... unless you mean one click importing of incomplete and erroneous listings that are sure to fxck you up.

name: Mitch Kosterman
description:
Actor, Traveller, Writer, Producer, Director, Grampa, Photographer
#ActuallyAutistic
tweet:
Tips For @Shopify Store Owners
RE: Item weight
Enter an item weight when you create your item listing. Some sales channels, such as Google and Facebook, will interpret a 0g weight as deceptive practice and deny you access to their channel.

name: Mitch Kosterman
description:
Actor, Traveller, Writer, Producer, Director, Grampa, Photographer
#ActuallyAutistic
tweet:
Tips For @Shopify Store Owners
RE: @spocketofficial
1. You will get emails from Spocket saying discontinued ("deactivated") items have been removed from your store. This is not always the case. Check the listing in your store and, to be prudent, check all items from that vendor.

tweet: 5/ Those channels will not let you, with anything but very specific settings - usually, the defaults.  In addition to some of the things you might know about, such as file size and type limitations, the main thing is, phones are not cameras. They try to help too much.
